cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the verification of a property (C-detectability) in a formal system (labeled Petri nets).
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes efficient approaches to verify C-detectability, which can be useful in AI applications.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the detectability of system states.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as Petri nets are a formalism used in programming language theory.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes efficient algorithms for verifying C-detectability.
